						<summary>

						<p>On a granite pillar in front of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>[Yādava Siṁhaṇa.]</p>						

						<p>Dated in <hi rend="italic">Saumya, Phālguna</hi> ba. 11.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of the village Garaṁjara or Galaṁjiri in Sindavāḍi-1000 by <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāni sarvādhikāri</hi> Sāṁva(ba)-paṇḍita for worship and offerings of god Ēlēśvara and for a feeding-house <hi rend="italic">(satra)</hi> for the merit of Siṁhaṇadeva-mahārāja. The gift was made over to Bhāva-brahma on the specified date. (cf. No. 122- A.R. No. 138 of 1954-55).</p>						

						</summary>
